# Commit title format:
# <type>(<scope>): <short imperative summary>
#
# Examples:
# feat(parser): add wildcard import support
# fix(cli): handle empty input arguments
# docs(readme): document local development setup
#
# Rules:
# - Prefer a title only.
# - Keep the title concise and specific.
# - Add a body only when it is necessary for review context.
# - If a body is needed, keep it to one or two short lines.
# - Do not write long background sections, motivation essays, or repeated change logs.
#
# Common types:
# feat     - new feature
# fix      - bug fix
# refactor - code restructuring without behavior change
# docs     - documentation only
# test     - tests added or updated
# chore    - maintenance / tooling / housekeeping
# ci       - CI configuration and automation
# perf     - performance improvements
# style    - formatting / style-only changes
# build    - build system or dependency changes
# revert   - revert a previous commit
#
# Template:
# <type>(<scope>): <short imperative summary>
#
# Optional body, only if needed:
# - 
